info.agentsInvolved: Agent: Lisa K., Provider: Dr. Todd R.
info.transcript: Customer: Hi, I want to confirm if my plan includes hypertension medication. Lisa: Yes, your plan covers prescribed drugs for hypertension. Is your medication from a network pharmacy? Customer: Yes, it's from Walgreens. Lisa: Great, you can submit your prescription online for reimbursement.

Customer: I was hospitalized last week. How do I file a claim? Sam: Please fill the claim form and upload your discharge summary within 60 days. Customer: What about the outpatient tests before admission? Sam: Those are covered too. Attach relevant bills to the same claim.

info.agentsInvolved: Agent: Tasha V., Provider: Nurse Helen
info.transcript: Customer: Can you tell me if arthritis treatment is covered? Tasha: Yes, as per your contract, outpatient visits for arthritis care are included. Customer: Do I need prior approval for physiotherapy? Tasha: For the first 10 sessions, no. After that, we need a provider's note.

Customer: What does a 10% co-pay mean for an outpatient visit costing $200? Bob: It means you pay $20, we cover $180. Customer: Is preventive checkup covered entirely? Bob: Yes, one per year without any copay.

Customer: Is mental health counseling for my son included? Grace: Outpatient counseling is covered up to 12 sessions annually. Customer: Are medications covered? Grace: Yes, but only for FDA-approved drugs.

info.agentsInvolved: Agent: Ann M., Provider: Dr. Lee Q.
info.transcript: Customer: My claim for diabetes supplies was denied. Why? Ann: It might be due to missing bills or exceeding annual limit. Please send your documents again for review. Dr. Lee: I can provide a fresh prescription if needed.
Customer: How do I check if a hospital is in-network? Amit: Search on our app or call this number. Customer: Is Cedars-Sinai covered? Amit: Yes, it is one of our accredited providers.

Customer: Does my insurance cover cancer screening? Rebecca: Yes. You can have one screening per year for specified cancers. Customer: Is there a copay? Rebecca: 10% co-pay applies unless it is preventive under your plan.

Customer: My card was not accepted at the hospital. What should I do? Dave: It may be a system issue. Please pay and keep receiptsâ€”submit them for reimbursement. Customer: How long does it take to get reimbursed? Dave: Around 2 weeks after claim submission.
Customer: Can I add maternity cover to my policy? Emma: Your current plan includes maternity care. For enhanced cover, you can upgrade in the next renewal cycle.

Customer: Can I add maternity cover to my policy? Fleece: No. Customer: This is not helpful, i want to file a complain and escalate about your rude behaviour. Fleece: Do whatever you want, I don't care.
